<!DOCTYPE html>
<%# Phase 15 calendar UX restructure — `/calendar` thin router page.
    A no-chrome shell that hands off to the JS view-router: the
    Stimulus controller reads localStorage and `replace`s to the
    persisted view, otherwise the meta-refresh fallback lands on the
    current month grid. Skipping the application layout keeps this
    page free of nav / footer flash during the redirect (a fresh
    chrome paint would briefly show before the JS replace fires). %>
<html data-theme-preference="<%= AppSetting.get('theme') || 'auto' %>">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <title>calendar ~ pito</title>
    <%# Server-side fallback for non-JS visits / failed Stimulus boot:
        meta-refresh to the current month grid after a tiny delay.
        The Stimulus controller will normally win this race and replace
        the URL before the meta-refresh fires. %>
    <meta http-equiv="refresh" content="1; url=<%= @month_path %>">
    <%= csrf_meta_tags %>
    <%= csp_meta_tag %>
    <%= javascript_importmap_tags %>
  </head>
  <body data-controller="calendar-view-router"
        data-calendar-view-router-month-path-value="<%= @month_path %>"
        data-calendar-view-router-schedule-path-value="<%= @schedule_path %>">
    <noscript>
      <p>Loading calendar… <a href="<%= @month_path %>">[continue]</a></p>
    </noscript>
  </body>
</html>
